cer for cyberpoint international a cyber security firm focused in abu dhabi and the uae market where he led pricing and cost proposal efforts to win over m in contract ceiling value awards prior to cyberpoint mr hunter was a financial leader and vice president at sra international inc a national publicly traded b government contractor where he successfully directed multiple transformational process improvement initiatives mr hunter has served in the us military as an intelligence analyst graduated from the university of virginia with a bs in accounting and received designation as a certified public accountant cpa mobile systems tony russell president of o’garahess  eisenhardt armoring company tony has  years of experience in the security and defense industry prior to joining o’gara tony was president of bae systems’ security  survivability business b in annual revenue and  employees across twelve sites the leading provider of body armor aircraft protection and vehicle survivability tony also served as senior vp of the ground vehicle survivability division and chief technology officer for armor holdings inc where he provided lifesaving products during a time of unprecedented surge he served as managing director of trasco in bremen germany where he initiated and executed growth from insolvency to record commercial armored vehicle output tony has his bs ms and phd in aerospace engineering michael reynolds vice president of program management mr reynolds is the vice president of program management operations and engineering he originally joined o’gara in june of  and has held many roles within the organization to include survivability manager director of engineering engineering director for the business capture programs  operations manager  transparent armor business segment vice president of engineering armor holdings and vice president of the bae systems advanced materials business segment mr reynolds graduated from the university of cincinnati with a bs in materials engineering and mba john richter controller – mobile systems division mr richter has been the controller for o’gara’s mobile systems division since january  prior to  he held several financial leadership positions with o’gara and predecessor companies beginning with the krollo’gara company in  after o’gara was acquired by armor holdings inc ahi in  mr richter served as vpfinance for ahi’s aerospace  defense group during a time of unprecedented growth for the company resulting in the sale of ahi to bae systems in  mr richter graduated from the university of cincinnati with a bba in accounting and is a cpa training  services kelly dollins vice president  training and operations mr dollins has held numerous leadership positions in federal law enforcement and the security and defense industry with over  years of experience in the security industry he has demonstrated superior leadership initiative technicaltactical expertise program enhancement creativity and solid performance success recent positions were department of state tactical subject matter expert incountry mentor indonesia and lead instructor special agent with the department of homeland security federal air marshal service law enforcement division special agent and team lead of the federal air marshal service special operations group and assistant director of security for the walt disney company he has been involved with facility operations security and training services contingency operations and high threat protection corporate security and cohesive team building he has served customers from the army navy air force marines as well as numerous government agencies including the dos cia dhs fbi and dia he is a combat veteran of the united states marine corps where he served proudly for  years on active duty rick holman senior vice president of operations mr holman is a  year veteran of naval special warfare he has proven executive leadership skills with extensive experience and success in strategic planning program development training training management and supervising daily operations being a former navy seal mr holman has extensive tactical training in the area of terrorist operations he is a subject matter expert in the area of vulnerability and physical security assessments he also has vast experience developing doctrines as well as planning and training publications the ogara group about us leadership profiles history training home about us our history leadership team contact us mobile systems overview vehicles history contact the ogara group training mobile systems like us on facebookprivacy policy   the ogara group all rights reserved wilfred t ogara  loveland oh  intelius sign in we found wilfred t ogara in loveland oh wilfred t ogara intelius found that wilfred t ogara is a male between  and  years old from loveland oh we have connected them to  addresses  phones and  relatives or associates also known as wilfred t ogara get report now age wilfred t ogara is in his s wilfred has lived in loveland oh cincinnati oh mason oh wilfreds relatives joseph ogara daniel ogara melissa ogara bill ogara wilfred t ogara zodiac signvirgo gendermale professional status president chief executive officer director at the ogara group inc get report now want to know more about wilfred get a comprehensive background report find full phone numbers and other contact information when available all from billions of available public records continue below for more details about wilfred or use our people search engine to find others get background check on wilfred t ogara get a criminal check on wilfred t ogara get a public record report on wilfred t ogara get a people search report on wilfred t ogara wilfred t ogaras contact information known cities lived in find out where wilfred t ogara has lived as well as wilfred t ogaras phone numbers and email addresses wilfred t ogara has lived in  states ohio address for wilfred t ogara  b p l loveland oh has lived in loveland oh cincinnati oh g